name: thedailybeast
text: President Trump’s campaign, the RNC, and three affiliated political groups raised nearly half a billion dollars from mid-October through late November, the campaign announced, including more than $200 million since Election Day https://t.co/7tWI68lD9l

name: thedailybeast
text: NEW: When the White House announced that President Trump would be hosting a summit to spotlight the progress on a COVID-19 vaccine, it came as news to many of the stakeholders involved in the vaccine production process https://t.co/onbrY81QOB

name: thedailybeast
text: According to two other senior administration officials, the summit appears to have been planned at the last minute as a PR show designed to allow Trump to take credit for the development and production of a COVID-19 vaccine  https://t.co/onbrY81QOB

name: thedailybeast
text: Officials said they expect the event to be largely political, with representatives of each industry feeling compelled to take time to thank the president for the vaccine development efforts that he’s delegated to others https://t.co/onbrY81QOB

name: thedailybeast
text: When asked if they would be required to attend the summit next week, one senior official working with the White House coronavirus task force said: “I hope not.” https://t.co/onbrY81QOB

name: thedailybeast
text: "The NFL has itself to blame," writes @carlsonmargaret. "It tried to play away the virus, wishing it off the field like player’s kneeling during the National Anthem or an epidemic of concussions. But no back-office PR team is a match for COVID." https://t.co/kL3rCxkmlb
